          • [ - ] SteveHyland - member since 03-Nov-12

            @Murgen- Surely if a club sells only half of it's tickets for home league matches, the club should be relocated to an area where more locals will be able to watch them? It doesn't matter if Monaco have 1 billion fans if only 8 to 9,000 of them travel to the games. The/any club needs support from the local area so it is self-sustaining and if fans don't/can't go to the games then what is the point having a club there? The fact is, Monaco has now become a vanity project just like the town itself. I'm sure when it was established, there was hope the club would grow and garner support from in and around Monaco but it doesn't. It's not so much the total number that go that matters, it's the % of the stadium filled on average and for Monaco that is a shocking 43%. The lowest in the prem is Aston Villa with 77% (the only team below 87%) and they aren't in the CL and contesting a domestic title. The average attendances by most teams in Ligue 1 in general is pathetic though, not just Monaco.
